"""
# Diploid encoding: 0 = WT/WT, 0.5 = MUT/WT, 1 = MUT/MUT
n_obs = 1
n_vars = int(1e8)
n_generations = 12
p_ups = [1e-5, 1e-6, 1e-7, 1e-8, 1e-9]

def divide_cell_with_mutations(mut0, mut1, n_vars, p_up):
    #mut0, mut1: sets of mutated site indices on two homologous chromosomes.
    #Returns: ((childA0, childA1), (childB0, childB1))
    #New mutations arise during replication on one chromatid and end up in only one daughter.
    childA0, childA1 = set(mut0), set(mut1)
    childB0, childB1 = set(mut0), set(mut1)

    for parent_mut, A, B in ((mut0, childA0, childB0), (mut1, childA1, childB1)):
        n_zero = n_vars - len(parent_mut)
        k_up = np.random.poisson(n_zero * p_up)

        new_pos = set()
        for _ in range(k_up):
            pos = np.random.randint(0, n_vars, dtype=np.int64)
            while (pos in parent_mut) or (pos in new_pos):
                pos = np.random.randint(0, n_vars, dtype=np.int64)
            new_pos.add(int(pos))

        for pos in new_pos:
            (A, B)[np.random.randint(0, 2)].add(pos)

    return (childA0, childA1), (childB0, childB1)

for p_up in p_ups:

    print("current p_up =", p_up)
    np.random.seed(42)
    cell_mut = [(set(), set()) for _ in range(n_obs)]
    lineage = [[i] for i in range(n_obs)]

    rows, cols, data = [], [], []
    obs_cell_id, obs_generation, obs_lineage = [], [], []

    global_row = 0
    for idx, lin in enumerate(lineage):
        obs_cell_id.append(f"cell_0_{idx}")
        obs_generation.append(0)
        obs_lineage.append("-".join(map(str, lin)))
        global_row += 1

    for gen in range(1, n_generations + 1):
        new_cell_mut, new_lineage = [], []

        for idx, ((mut0, mut1), lin) in enumerate(zip(cell_mut, lineage)):
            (childA0, childA1), (childB0, childB1) = divide_cell_with_mutations(
                mut0, mut1, n_vars, p_up
            )

            for daughter_idx, (c0, c1) in enumerate(((childA0, childA1), (childB0, childB1))):
                row_idx = global_row
                global_row += 1

                both = c0 & c1
                hemi = c0 ^ c1

                for c in both:
                    rows.append(row_idx); cols.append(c); data.append(1.0)
                for c in hemi:
                    rows.append(row_idx); cols.append(c); data.append(0.5)

                obs_cell_id.append(f"cell_{gen}_{idx * 2 + daughter_idx}")
                obs_generation.append(gen)
                new_lin = lin + [idx * 2 + daughter_idx]
                obs_lineage.append("-".join(map(str, new_lin)))

                new_cell_mut.append((set(c0), set(c1)))
                new_lineage.append(new_lin)

        cell_mut = new_cell_mut
        lineage = new_lineage

    X_sparse = sp.csr_matrix(
        (data, (rows, cols)),
        shape=(global_row, n_vars),
        dtype=np.float32,
    )

    obs = pd.DataFrame(
        {"cell_id": obs_cell_id, "generation": obs_generation, "lineage": obs_lineage}
    )

    adata = ad.AnnData(X=X_sparse, obs=obs)
    fname = f"./diploid_{n_generations}_generations_{n_obs}cells_{n_vars:.0e}mutations_{p_up:.0e}.h5ad"
    adata.write(fname)
    print(f"Saved: {fname}")

os.makedirs(outdir, exist_ok=True)

def fmt_p_up(x: float) -> str:
    return f"{x:.0e}"

for mu in p_ups:
    p_up_str = fmt_p_up(mu)
    infile = infile_template.format(p_up=p_up_str)

    print("\n" + "=" * 80)
    print(f"Processing p_up = {p_up_str}")
    print(f"Input file: {infile}")

    adata = ad.read_h5ad(infile)
    print("Raw adata.shape:", adata.shape)

    adata = filter_adata_by_mutation_nnz(adata, min_nnz=2)
    print("Filtered adata.shape:", adata.shape)

    sc.pp.pca(adata)
    explained_var = adata.uns["pca"]["variance_ratio"]
    explained_var_cum = explained_var.cumsum()

    kl = KneeLocator(
        range(1, len(explained_var) + 1),
        explained_var,
        curve="convex",
        direction="decreasing"
    )
    elbow_PC = kl.elbow
    #elbow_PC = int(np.argmax(explained_var_cum >= 0.8) + 1) if np.any(explained_var_cum >= 0.8) else 10

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 4))
    ax.plot(range(1, len(explained_var) + 1), explained_var, "o-", markersize=3, label="Individual explained variance")
    ax.plot(range(1, len(explained_var) + 1), explained_var_cum, "s-", markersize=3, label="Cumulative explained variance")
    ax.axvline(elbow_PC, color="r", linestyle="--", label=f"Elbow at PC {elbow_PC}")
    ax.set_xlabel("Principal Component")
    ax.set_ylabel("Explained Variance Ratio")
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_title("Scree plot of PCA")

    elbow_out = os.path.join(outdir, f"p01.PC_elbow_mutations_{p_up_str}_plot.pdf")
    #fig.savefig(elbow_out, dpi=300, bbox_inches="tight")
    #plt.show()
    #plt.close(fig)

    print("Automatically detected elbow PC number:", elbow_PC)
    print("Saved elbow plot:", elbow_out)
    pc2d_out = os.path.join(outdir, f"p02.Generation_2dPC_{p_up_str}_plot.pdf")
    adata.obs["generation"] = adata.obs["generation"].astype(int).astype("category")
    #plot_snv_pca_by_group(adata, pcx=1, pcy=2, group_by = "generation", group_colors=gen_colors, savepath=pc2d_out)

    # Subset to 10 cells in each generation
    rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)
    gen = np.asarray(adata.obs["generation"]).astype(int)
    unique_gens = np.sort(np.unique(gen))

    keep_idx = []
    for g in unique_gens:
        idx_g = np.where(gen == g)[0]
        take = 10 if idx_g.size > 10 else idx_g.size
        keep_idx.append(rng.choice(idx_g, size=take, replace=False))

    keep_idx = np.sort(np.concatenate(keep_idx))
    adata_sub = adata[keep_idx, :].copy()
    print("Subset adata_sub.shape:", adata_sub.shape)

    # Plot NJ trees
    adata_sub.obs.loc[:, "group"] = (adata_sub.obs["lineage"].astype("string").str.split("-").str[: (n_group + 1)].str.join("-"))
    tree_out = os.path.join(outdir, f"p03.Subset_NJ_tree_K{elbow_PC}_{p_up_str}_plot.pdf")
    tree = build_and_plot_nj(adata_sub, figsize=(10, 10), group_colors=group_colors, K=elbow_PC, leafcolor_onside=True,
        group_key="group", show_legend=True, savepath=tree_out)
    print("Saved NJ tree:", tree_out)

N_SPLITS_IF_C = 4    # If n_cells in a group_generation > n_cells_min_split, split into N parts
n_cells_min_split = 4
n_group = 2
min_nnz = 2
group_colors = {'0': "#31688E", '0-0': "#35B779", '0-1': "#7550a6", '0-0-0': "#abff03", '0-0-1': "#3bed82", '0-1-2': "#f294df", '0-1-3': "#ed7e98"}

p_ups2 = [1e-8, 1e-9]
infile_template = "h5ad_simu/diploid_12_generations_1cell_1e+08mutations_{p_up}.h5ad"
outdir = "Plots_simu_data/"
os.makedirs(outdir, exist_ok=True)

def fmt_p_up(x: float) -> str:
    # Produce strings like "1e-08", "1e-09" to match your filename style
    return f"{x:.0e}"

rng = np.random.default_rng(42)

for mu in p_ups2:
    p_up_str = fmt_p_up(mu)
    infile = infile_template.format(p_up=p_up_str)

    print("\n" + "=" * 80)
    print(f"Processing p_up = {p_up_str}")
    print(f"Input file: {infile}")

    adata = ad.read_h5ad(infile)
    print("Raw adata.shape:", adata.shape)

    adata.obs.loc[:, "group"] = (
        adata.obs["lineage"].astype("string").str.split("-").str[: (n_group + 1)].str.join("-")
    )
    adata.obs["group_generation"] = (
        "g" + adata.obs["generation"].astype(str) + "-l" + adata.obs["group"].astype(str)
    )

    X = adata.X
    is_sparse = sp.issparse(X)

    group = adata.obs["group_generation"].astype(str).to_numpy()
    uniq_groups = pd.unique(group)
    orig_obs_names = adata.obs_names.to_numpy()

    X_blocks, idx_names = [], []
    obs_group, obs_sub, obs_ncells, obs_mode = [], [], [], []

    for g in uniq_groups:
        idx = np.flatnonzero(group == g)
        n = idx.size
        if n == 0:
            continue

        if n > n_cells_min_split:
            perm = rng.permutation(idx)

            q, r = divmod(n, N_SPLITS_IF_C)  # First r parts have (q+1) cells, remaining parts have q cells
            start = 0

            for k in range(1, N_SPLITS_IF_C + 1):
                size = q + (1 if k <= r else 0)
                part = perm[start : start + size]
                start += size

                if size == 0:
                    continue

                X_part = X[part, :]

                if is_sparse:
                    mu_vec = X_part.sum(axis=0)
                    mu_vec = np.asarray(mu_vec).ravel() / float(size)
                    X_blocks.append(sp.csr_matrix(mu_vec))
                else:
                    mu_vec = np.asarray(X_part.mean(axis=0)).ravel()
                    X_blocks.append(mu_vec.reshape(1, -1))

                idx_names.append(f"{g}_sub{k}")
                obs_group.append(g)
                obs_sub.append(k)
                obs_ncells.append(int(size))
                obs_mode.append("mean_of_subset")

        else:
            # n <= n_cells_min_split: retain original cell rows
            X_part = X[idx, :]

            if is_sparse:
                X_blocks.append(X_part.tocsr())
            else:
                X_blocks.append(np.asarray(X_part))

            new_names = [f"{nm}_sub1" for nm in orig_obs_names[idx]]
            idx_names.extend(new_names)
            obs_group.extend([g] * n)
            obs_sub.extend([1] * n)
            obs_ncells.extend([1] * n)
            obs_mode.extend(["original_cell"] * n)

    # ---------- Merge into a new AnnData ----------
    if is_sparse:
        X_new = sp.vstack(X_blocks, format="csr")
    else:
        X_new = np.vstack(X_blocks)

    obs_new = pd.DataFrame(
        {"group": obs_group, "sub": obs_sub, "n_cells": obs_ncells, "mode": obs_mode},
        index=idx_names,
    )

    adata_new = ad.AnnData(X=X_new, obs=obs_new, var=adata.var.copy())
    adata_new.var_names = adata.var_names.copy()

    # Convert group_generation "g{generation}-l{group}" back to plain "{group}"
    adata_new.obs["group"] = adata_new.obs["group"].astype(str).str.replace(r"^g\d+-l", "", regex=True)

    # ---------- Downstream steps (keep your existing functions/variables) ----------
    #adata_new = revise_snv_ratio(adata_new)
    adata_new = filter_adata_by_mutation_nnz(adata_new, min_nnz=min_nnz)

    sc.pp.pca(adata_new)
    explained_var = adata_new.uns["pca"]["variance_ratio"]
    explained_var_cum = explained_var.cumsum()

    kl = KneeLocator(
        range(1, len(explained_var) + 1),
        explained_var,
        curve="convex",
        direction="decreasing",
    )
    elbow_PC = kl.elbow
    print("elbow_PC:", elbow_PC)

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 4))
    ax.plot(range(1, len(explained_var) + 1), explained_var, "o-", markersize=3, label="Individual explained variance")
    ax.plot(range(1, len(explained_var) + 1), explained_var_cum, "s-", markersize=3, label="Cumulative explained variance")
    ax.axvline(elbow_PC, color="r", linestyle="--", label=f"Elbow at PC {elbow_PC}")
    ax.set_xlabel("Principal Component")
    ax.set_ylabel("Explained Variance Ratio")
    ax.legend()

    elbow_out = os.path.join(outdir, f"p01.PC_elbow_mutations_recover_withmerge_{p_up_str}_plot.pdf")
    fig.savefig(elbow_out, dpi=300, bbox_inches="tight")
    plt.show()
    plt.close(fig)
    print("Saved elbow plot:", elbow_out)

    print("Subset adata_new.shape:", adata_new.shape)
    tree_out = os.path.join(outdir, f"p03.Subset_NJ_tree_recover_withmerge_K{elbow_PC}_{p_up_str}_plot.pdf")
    tree = build_and_plot_nj(
        adata_new, figsize=(10, 10), group_colors=group_colors, K=elbow_PC, leafcolor_onside=True,
        group_key="group", show_leaf_labels=False, show_legend=True, savepath=tree_out, print_tree_info=True, return_tree_info=True)
    print("Saved NJ tree:", tree_out)
